					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12540690#post-4364379</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12540690/scp-4778#post-4364379</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 15 Sep 2019 11:09:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Tanhony</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>776854</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I enjoyed this. The idea of these whales repairing the environment just by existing is a really nice starting hook, and the detail you go into with how exactly they're doing it adds a good sense of verisimilitude to the article. World-building is always something I appreciate in articles, too, and the mention of the Parazoology Division scratches that itch nicely.</p> <p>The ending, with it being implied that the Foundation are going to take steps to preserve the species to repair the Earth - normalcy be damned - is a really nice way to leave it off, too. If I had to say something that didn't quite work for me, it'd be the discovery log - it's really nicely put together, with the communications between the ship and the base, but I don't know how much it really adds to the article.</p> <p>Still, there's a hearty +1 here from me!</p> <p><sub><strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Opinions expressed in this review do not reflect the opinions of SCP Wiki staff as a whole. Please respond to <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tanhony" >Tanhony</a></span> or contact the captain of the Site Criticism Team, <span class="printuser"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" >SoullessSingularity</a></span>, for any questions or concerns relating to this review.</sub></p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
